name: Jason Mikula
tweet: The first financial bubbles took place in England, France, & Netherlands around 1720.  When they popped, it caused a cultural & regulatory backlash ‚Äî incl the passage of the ‚ÄúBubble Act‚Äù in England, & a near freeze in joint stock companies in all 3 countries for nearly 100 years.

name: Jason Mikula
tweet: Bubbles require:  ‚úÖ a marketable asset/liquidity  ‚úÖ credit & leverage (margin/options)  ‚úÖ speculation, including potentially unsubstantiated or misleading encouragement by market participants who stand to benefit (üëÄ @elonmusk , @chamath )

tweet: Currently reading ‚ÄúBoom & Bust: Global History of Financial Bubbles‚Äù  If you‚Äôre looking to put current trends in public equities ($TSLA), SPACs, crypto ($DOGE) into a historical context, highly recommend getting this book.   https://t.co/DM2FJRU6sH
